(secondQuint)Use of MUAC as Basic Criterion for Admission, Follow-up and Exit From the Ambulatory Nutrition Program.

 This is a first operational experiment using Mid-Upper Arm Circumference (MUAC) as the single anthropometric criterion for the admission, monitoring and exit of the management of uncomplicated SAM (Severe Acute Malnutrition) in Niger, specific data as well as data from routine program will be collected to allow comprehensive documentation of all relevant results and operational implications of this new model.

 The experiment based on the use of the single anthropometric threshold for admission of a Mid-Upper Arm Circumference (MUAC) 120 mm, will identify how children respond to treatment and benefit of the spectrum of acute malnutrition.

